# Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) Rules

## Initialization and Permissions
- Initialize FCM in `TabsPage` using `FCMService.instance.initialize()`
- Permission requests should use `PermissionService.instance.requestPermissionWithFCM()`
- After permission granted, call `FCMService.instance.initialize()` to set up handlers

## Platform-Specific Permission Logic
- Android:
  - Android 13+ (API level 33+): Request explicit `POST_NOTIFICATIONS` permission using `Permission.notification.request()`
  - Android 12 and below: No explicit permission needed, return `true` by default
  - Check Android version with `DeviceInfoPlugin().androidInfo.version.sdkInt >= 33`

- iOS:
  - Use Firebase Messaging API for permission: `messaging.requestPermission()`
  - Configure presentation options: `setForegroundNotificationPresentationOptions()`
  - Get APNS token after permission granted: `getAPNSToken()`
  - Check permission status: `messaging.getNotificationSettings()`
  - Permission is granted if `authorizationStatus == AuthorizationStatus.authorized` or `provisional`

## Token Management
- Get FCM token: `PermissionService.instance.getToken()`
- Register token with backend: `FCMService.instance.registerToken()` or `saveTokenToServer(token)`
- The backend endpoint for token registration is `$apiEndpoint/api/notifications/register-device/`

## Notification Preferences
- Get preferences: `NotificationPreferencesService.instance.getPreferences(forceRefresh: true)`
- Update preferences: `NotificationPreferencesService.instance.updatePreferences()`
- When permission is denied, preserve user's server-side preferences (don't overwrite to `false`). The `updatePreferences()` method blocks enabling preferences without OS permission, but `getPreferences()` always returns the user's saved values.
- Reset session flag on app start: `NotificationPreferencesService.instance.resetSessionFlag()`

## Notification Navigation
- Background/terminated app navigation handled in `_firebaseMessagingBackgroundHandler`
- In-app navigation uses `_processMessageData()` with action types:
  - 'view_transaction': Navigates to transaction details
  - 'view_budget': Navigates to budget details
- Implement deep linking by extracting navigation data from message payload